  "title": "Requiring instantsearch.js leads to lodash error",
  "body": "Calling `var instantsearch = require('instantsearch.js');` causes `Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property '0' of undefined(…)` on this line in lodash.\n\n``` js\nvar keys = require('lodash/object/keys');\n```\n\nSeems like a dependency problem. This started happening after I updated my project to `react@15.0.1` and `instantsearch.js@1.4.5`. I verified that lodash is properly installed in node_modules.\n",
